// Emit config for `bun run build`. tsconfig.json is the typecheck/editor
// config and deliberately covers src/__tests__ — but tsc here emits rather
// than just checking, and package.json ships `files: ["dist"]`, so building
// with that config would publish 116 compiled test artifacts to npm.
//
// The narrower `types` is also load-bearing, not tidiness: the CLI is built
// `--target=node` and runs on node (engines.node >= 22), while the tests run
// under bun. Withholding bun's globals from the production compile is what
// keeps a real `Bun.serve` out of src/ — it would typecheck and then die for
// npm users. (src/commands/generate/index.ts only emits one inside a
// template string, which is why it compiles today.)
{
  "extends": "./tsconfig.json",
  "compilerOptions": {
    "types": ["node"]
  },
  "exclude": ["node_modules", "dist", "src/__tests__"]
}
